0constitution%20provides%20a%20unique%20power%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20do%20%E2%80%9Ccomplete%20justice%E2%80%9D%20between%20the%20parties%2C%20where%2C%20at%20times%2C%20the%20law%20or%20statute%20may%20not%20provide%20a%20remedy.%20In%20those%20situations%2C%20the%20court%20can%20put%20an%20end%20to%20a%20dispute%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20would%20fit%20the%20facts%20of%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Trivedi%20clarified%2C%20%E2%80%9CThese%20powers%2C%20though%20are%20of%20a%20very%20wide%20amplitude%20to%20do%20complete%20justice%20between%20the%20parties%2C%20cannot%20be%20used%20to%20supplant%20the%20substantive%20law%20applicable%20to%20the%20case%20or%20to%20the%20cause%20under%20consideration%20of%20the%20court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERelying%20on%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20observation%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1666530%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESupreme%20Court%20Bar%20Association%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ecase%2C%20the%20Bench%20held%20that%20Article%20142%2C%20even%20with%20the%20width%20of%20its%20amplitude%20cannot%20be%20used%20to%20build%20a%20new%20edifice%20where%20none%20existed%20earlier%2C%20by%20ignoring%20the%20express%20statutory%20provisions%20dealing%20with%20a%20subject%20and%20thereby%20to%20achieve%20something%20indirectly%20which%20cannot%20be%20achieved%20directly.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20case%20at%20hand%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2022%2F30512%2F30512_2022_6_1501_47350_Judgement_04-Oct-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EUnion%20Bank%20of%20India%20vs%20Rajat%20Infrastructure%20Pvt%20Ltd%20%26amp%3B%20Others%20(Respondents)%20and%20M%2Fs%20Sunview%20Assets%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(Applicant)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2022%2F30512%2F30512_2022_6_1501_47350_Judgement_04-Oct-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethe%20appellant%20bank%20initiated%20the%20proceedings%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1089596%2F%5C%22%3ESection%2013%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20the%20Securitisation%20and%20Reconstruction%20of%20Financial%20Assets%20and%20Enforcement%20of%20Security%20Interest%20Act%2C%202002%20(SARFAESI%20Act)%20in%20respect%20of%20the%20Subject%20Property%20mortgaged%20with%20it.%20The%20bank%20had%20issued%20a%20notice%20for%20an%20e-auction%20sale%20of%20the%20said%20property%20under%20the%20Act%2C%20scheduling%20the%20auction%20sale%20on%20July%204%2C%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20applicant%20claimed%20to%20be%20the%20highest%20bidder%20for%20a%20sum%20of%20Rs%2065.62%20crore.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20earlier%20permitted%20the%20applicant%20to%20pay%20a%20balance%20sale%20price%20of%20Rs%2049%2C%2021%2C%2050%2C000%20by%20April%2030%2C%202020%2C%20in%20view%20of%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%20On%20May%2012%2C%202020%2C%20the%20court%20further%20extended%20the%20time%20to%20deposit%20the%20remaining%20amount%20with%20interest%20at%20the%20lending%20rate%20till%20two%20months%20after%20the%20lockdown%20was%20lifted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20depositing%20Rs%2014%2C%2080%2C00%2C000%2C%20the%20applicant%20again%20sought%20an%20extension%20of%20time%20to%20pay%20the%20balance%20amount%20in%202022.%20The%20applicant%20deposited%20a%20further%20amount%20of%20Rs%2034%2C41%2C50%2C000%20with%20the%20bank%20on%20July%2022%2C%202022%2C%20and%20later%20paid%20the%20amount%20due%20as%20interest%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%20noted%20that%20it%20was%20incumbent%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20applicant%20to%20state%20as%20to%20when%20exactly%20the%20lockdown%20was%20lifted%2C%20what%20was%20the%20lending%20rate%20of%20interest%20at%20the%20relevant%20time%2C%20and%20how%20much%20amount%20the%20applicant%20was%20required%20to%20pay%20towards%20the%20balance%20sale%20price%20and%20towards%20the%20interest%20for%20the%20period%20starting%20from%20March%2020%2C%202020%20till%20the%20deposit%20was%20made.%20The%20Bench%20observed%20that%20the%20applicant%20had%20failed%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20orders%2C%20by%20not%20making%20the%20deposit%20of%20the%20entire%20balance%20amount%20with%20interest%20within%20two%20months%20from%20February%202022%2C%20even%20if%20a%20lenient%20view%20is%20taken%20that%20the%20period%20of%20limitation%20had%20stood%20extended%20on%20account%20of%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArticle%20142%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20invoked%3A%20SC%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20applicant%E2%80%99s%20senior%20counsel%2C%20Dushyant%20Dave%2C%20submitted%20that%20the%20court%20should%20use%20its%20inherent%20powers%20under%20Article%20142%20of%20the%20constitution%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.ipleaders.in%2Finherent-powers-of-the-court%2F%5C%22%3ESection%20148%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Civil%20Procedure%20Code%20(CPC)%20to%20treat%20the%20partial%20deposits%20made%20within%20the%20deadline%20as%20due%20compliance%20with%20its%20order%20and%20extend%20the%20time%20limit%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%2C%20however%2C%20rejected%20the%20submission%20saying%20it%20is%20contrary%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinancialservices.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FSARFAESI0001.pdf%5C%22%3E%20Rule%209%20of%20the%20SARFAESI%20Rules%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20which%20the%20balance%20amount%20of%20purchase%20price%20payable%20has%20to%20be%20paid%20by%20the%20purchaser%20to%20the%20authorised%20officer%20on%20or%20before%20the%2015th%20day%20of%20the%20confirmation%20of%20sale%20or%20such%20extended%20period%20as%20may%20be%20agreed%20upon%20in%20writing%20between%20the%20purchaser%20and%20the%20secured%20creditor%2C%20in%20any%20case%20not%20extending%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20cannot%20be%20gainsaid%20that%20the%20court%20in%20the%20exercise%20of%20powers%20under%20Article%20142%20cannot%20ignore%20any%20substantive%20statutory%20provision%20dealing%20with%20the%20subject%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Bench%20observed.%20Even%20Section%20148%20of%20CPC%20does%20not%20permit%20the%20court%20to%20extend%20the%20time%20limit%20beyond%2030%20days%20of%20the%20time%20limit%20fixed%20by%20the%20court%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHaving%20held%20so%2C%20the%20Bench%20dismissed%20the%20applicant%E2%80%99s%20miscellaneous%20application%20seeking%20direction%20against%20the%20appellant%20bank%20for%20the%20issuance%20of%20the%20sale%20certificate%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20the%20applicant%20had%20made%20full%20and%20final%20payment%20of%20the%20auction%20amount%20with%20interest%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20order%20dated%20May%2012%2C%202020%2C%20as%20not%20maintainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%20recalled%20that%20the%20trend%20emerging%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20filing%20repeated%20applications%2C%20styled%20as%20miscellaneous%20applications%20(MAs)%2C%20without%20any%20legal%20foundation%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-miscellaneous-application-modification-judgment-183540%5C%22%3Estrongly%20deprecated%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20earlier.%20The%20court%20had%20held%20that%20filing%20MAs%20was%20becoming%20a%20preferred%20course%20for%20those%20with%20resources%20to%20pursue%20strategies%20to%20avoid%20compliance%20with%20judicial%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20judicial%20pronouncement%20cannot%20be%20subject%20to%20modification%20once%20the%20judgment%20has%20been%20pronounced%2C%20by%20filing%20a%20miscellaneous%20application.%20Filing%20a%20miscellaneous%20application%20seeking%20modification%2Fclarification%20of%20a%20judgment%20is%20not%20envisaged%20in%20law.%20Further%2C%20it%20is%20a%20settled%20legal%20principle%20that%20one%20cannot%20do%20indirectly%20what%20one%20cannot%20do%20directly%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20had%20held%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2014%2F14414%2F14414_2014_34_1501_29602_Judgement_31-Aug-2021.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESupertech%20Limited%20vs%20Emerald%20Court%20Owner%20Resident%20Welfare%20Association%20and%20Others%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2021).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%2C%20however%2C%20permitted%20the%20Applicant%20to%20take%20recourse%20to%20any%20other%20remedy%20permissible%20under%20the%20law%20for%20the%20prayers%20sought%20in%20the%20application%2C%20or%20to%20file%20appropriate%20proceedings%20seeking%20refund%20of%20the%20amount%20deposited%20with%20the%20bank%2C%20as%20may%20be%20permissible%20under%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696492222000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcourts-sweeping-powers-under-article-142-cant-be-used-to-override-substantive-law-sc%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Article%20142%20of%20the%20constitution%20confers%20a%20unique%20power%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20do%20'complete%20justice'%20between%20the%20parties%20where%20the%20law%20may%20not%20provide%20a%20remedy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcourts-sweeping-powers-under-article-142-cant-be-used-to-override-substantive-law-sc%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chinese%20Nuclear%20Submarine%20Suffers%20Catastrophic%20Failure%3A%20What%20We%20Know%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20alleged%20%26quot%3Bcatastrophic%20failure%26quot%3B%20of%20a%20Chinese%20nuclear-powered%20submarine%20caused%20the%20death%20of%2055%20sailors%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20said.%20The%20news%20report%20was%20based%20on%20leaked%20British%20intelligence%20that%20said%20the%20incident%20took%20place%20in%20Yellow%20Sea%20on%20August%2021.%20The%20submarine%20was%20identified%20as%20093-417%2C%20which%20was%20armed%20with%20torpedoes.%20China%20has%20denied%20the%20loss%20of%20any%20submarine%20in%20the%20region%2C%20but%20the%20news%20report%20has%20been%20making%20waves%20across%20the%20world.%20The%20captain%20and%2021%20officers%20are%20among%20the%20dead%2C%20the%20report%20further%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happened%20to%20the%20Chinese%20submarine%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thetimes.co.uk%2Farticle%2Fchina-kills-own-sailors-with-trap-set-for-us-and-british-vessels-75wdfkc2p%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%C2%A0Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%2C%20the%20submarine%20was%20caught%20in%20a%20'chain%20and%20anchor%20obstacle'%2C%20which%20was%20laid%20there%20to%20trap%20the%20submarines%20of%20the%20US%20and%20allied%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20reportedly%20resulted%20in%20systems%20failure%20that%20required%20six%20hours%20of%20repair%20before%20the%20submarine%20could%20resurface.%20By%20then%2C%20the%20oxygen%20systems%20malfunctioned%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20deaths%20of%2055%20crew%20members%20from%20hypoxia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20on-board%20oxygen%20system%20poisoned%20the%20crew%20after%20a%20catastrophic%20failure%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20British%20intelligence%20officials%20said%20in%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EConcerns%20about%20water%20contamination%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20no%20independent%20confirmation%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchinas-nuclear-submarine-suffers-catastrophic-failure-55-dead-report-4448320%5C%22%3Esuspected%20loss%20of%20the%20Chinese%20submarine%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20come%20to%20the%20public%20domain%2C%20experts%20have%20spoken%20about%20what%20this%20means%20for%20marine%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20incident%20has%20occurred%2C%20the%20global%20silence%20is%20perplexing.%20A%20nuclear%20submarine%20sinkin