20employee%20of%20the%20media%20outlet%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20editorial%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Fundeclared-emergency-the-hindu-editorial-on-the-arrests-in-the-newsclick-case%2Farticle67380803.ece%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CEven%20for%20a%20government%20that%20has%20shown%20itself%20to%20be%20intolerant%20of%20critical%20journalism%2C%20the%20actions%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party-led%20regime%20on%20the%20news%20website%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20smack%20of%20extreme%20vendetta%20and%20brazen%20harassment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20editorial%20delves%20into%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20arrested%20persons%20have%20not%20yet%20been%20given%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR)%2C%20that%20Purkayastha%20has%20been%20granted%20protection%20by%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20from%20arrest%2C%20and%20that%20a%20lower%20court%20has%20also%20dismissed%20a%20complaint%20filed%20by%20the%20income%20tax%20department%20against%20the%20media%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20government%20claims%20that%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20proximate%20to%20the%20Chinese%20government%20and%20pushing%20its%20agenda%20against%20India%2C%20the%20editorial%20notes%20that%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20have%20not%20been%20able%20to%20point%20to%20%E2%80%9Cany%20specific%20article%20on%20the%20site%20that%20amounted%20to%20illegal%20propaganda%20against%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGovernment%20representatives%20first%20engaged%20in%20a%20systematic%20vilification%20and%20disinformation%20campaign%20against%20the%20site%20based%20on%20this%20article.%20Tuesday%E2%80%99s%20actions%20seem%20driven%20by%20an%20impulse%20to%20scapegoat%20a%20media%20outlet%20and%20to%20bring%20about%2C%20therefore%2C%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20critical%20journalism.%20No%20government%20can%20or%20should%20so%20brazenly%20target%20journalists%20solely%20based%20on%20suspicion%20about%20its%20funding%20and%20thereby%20undermine%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%2C%20which%20is%20guaranteed%20under%20the%20Constitution%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Fundeclared-emergency-the-hindu-editorial-on-the-arrests-in-the-newsclick-case%2Farticle67380803.ece%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20raids%20and%20arrests%20%E2%80%9Cunderlines%20apprehensions%20of%20Police-ED%20being%20weaponised%20and%20a%20draconian%20law%20being%20deployed%20to%20intimidate%20a%20media%20organisation%E2%80%9D.%20The%20arrests%20and%20raids%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E%20editorial%20says%2C%20raise%20%E2%80%9Cgrave%20questions%20about%20press%20freedom%2C%20a%20crucial%20part%20of%20the%20citizens%E2%80%99%20fundamental%20right%20to%20know%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20noting%20that%20the%20state%20is%20fully%20within%20its%20rights%20to%20investigate%20the%20funding%20allegations%20against%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20editorial%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fdrawing-lines-in-cauvery-waters-8968776%2F%5C%22%3Esays%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20state%20should%20not%20brazenly%20wrest%20more%20power%20to%20circumvent%20restraints%20under%20a%20stringent%20law%20that%2C%20in%20this%20matter%2C%20is%20clearly%20uncalled-for%20%E2%80%93%20in%20which%20the%20general%20principles%20of%20criminal%20law%20are%20reversed%2C%20timelines%20are%20relaxed%20for%20filing%20chargesheets%20and%20bail%20is%20immensely%20more%20difficult.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20editorial%20recalled%20the%20observations%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20made%20in%20April%20this%20year%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-media-one-sealed-cover-analysis%5C%22%3EMediaOne%20case%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Chief%20Justice%20had%20said%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20security%20claims%20cannot%20be%20made%20out%20of%20thin%20air%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20state%20using%20national%20security%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctool%E2%80%9D%20to%20deny%20citizens%20remedies%20is%20not%20compatible%20with%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%20The%20CJI-led%20Bench%20had%20also%20flagged%20why%20the%20protection%20of%20critical%20views%20is%20vital%20to%20the%20health%20of%20the%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20described%20the%20raids%20and%20attacks%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fopinion%2Fanother-blow-editorial-on-police-raids-perpetrated-on-newsclick-and-press-freedom-under-pm-modi%2Fcid%2F1971129%5C%22%3Eunbridled%20authoritarianism%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20being%20exercised%20by%20the%20Modi%20government.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20charges%20(against%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E)%20should%20be%20examined%20neutrally%20in%20a%20court%20of%20law.%20But%20the%20attempt%20to%20malign%20the%20organisation%20%E2%80%93%20in%20effect%2C%20the%20tiny%20media%20fraternity%20pursuing%20independent%20news%20%E2%80%93%20even%20before%20the%20accusations%20have%20been%20proved%20in%20court%20is%20yet%20another%20instance%20of%20Mr.%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20government%20exercising%20unbridled%20authoritarianism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECalling%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20campaign%E2%80%9D%20to%20protect%20press%20freedom%2C%20the%20editorial%20notes%20that%20the%20action%20against%20NewsClick%2C%20or%20any%20media%20organisation%20which%20does%20not%20toe%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20line%2C%20should%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccollective%20threat%E2%80%9D%20to%20Indian%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20must%20be%20a%20public%20campaign%20to%20raise%20awareness%20that%20the%20weakening%20and%20the%20corresponding%20transformation%20of%20the%20media%20into%20cheerleaders%20of%20the%20regime%20have%20serious%20repercussions%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20both%20the%20nation%20and%20its%20citizens.%20India%E2%80%99s%20media%20space%20is%20divided%3B%20the%20divisions%20are%20the%20result%20of%20competition%20and%20differences%20in%20political%20fidelities.%20It%20must%20unite%2C%20if%20only%20for%20a%20while%2C%20to%20assess%20the%20depths%20of%20the%20crisis.%20For%20the%20crisis%20is%20existential%20in%20nature.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696487236000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F12%2Fpress-freedom-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fanother-blow-for-press-freedom-under-modi-govt-say-newspapers-on-newsclick-raids-arrests%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Editorials%20by%20English%20language%20newspapers%20said%20even%20for%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20which%20has%20been%20'intolerant'%20of%20critical%20journalism%2C%20the%20'NewsClick'%20episode%20marks%20a%20new%20low%20in%20terms%20of%20muzzling%20press%20freedom.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fanother-blow-for-press-freedom-under-modi-govt-say-newspapers-on-newsclick-raids-arrests%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fresh%20violence%20in%20Manipur%2C%20two%20houses%20torched%20in%20Imphal%20West%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696487046000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104179170%2Cimgsize-1790178.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fimphal%2Ffresh-violence-in-manipur-2-houses-torched-in-imphal-west-district%2Farticleshow%2F104179190.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fimphal%2Ffresh-violence-in-manipur-2-houses-torched-in-imphal-west-district%2Farticleshow%2F104179190.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BEx%20Wife%20Inflicted%20Cruelty%2C%20Agony%20On%20Shikhar%20Dhawan%26quot%3B%3A%20What%20Delhi%20Court%20Said%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20Delhi%20Court%20on%20Wednesday%20granted%20divorce%20to%20cricketer%20Shikhar%20Dhawan%20on%20grounds%20of%20%26quot%3Bcruelty%26quot%3B%20inflicted%20on%20the%20cricketer%20by%20his%20estranged%20wife%20Aesha%20Dhawan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Dhawan%20and%20Aesha%20Mukherjee%20married%20in%202012%20and%20have%20a%2010-year-old%20son%2C%20Zoraver%20Dhawan.%20Both%20Aesha%20and%20Zoraver%20are%20Australian%20citizens.%20Aesha%20was%20previously%20married%20and%20has%20two%20daughters%20with%20first%20husband.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFamily%20Court%20Judge%20Harish%20Kumar%20accepted%20Mr%20Dhawan's%20accusations%20against%20his%20wife%20after%20it%20stated%20that%20she%20was%20unable%20to%20prove%20the%20allegations%20as%20false.%20The%20judge%20observed%20that%20Mr%20Dhawan%20was%20subjected%20to%20mental%20agony%20by%20his%20wife%20who%20forced%20him%20into%20being%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Blong%20distance%20marriage%26quot%3B%20by%20living%20in%20Australia%20and%20keeping%20him%20away%20from%20his%20son%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3EHere's%20what%20the%20court%20said%20while%20granting%20the%20divorce%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BMr%20Dhawan%20has%20been%20through%20immense%20agony%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20petition%2C%20Mr%20Dhawan%20claimed%20that%20his%20wife%20has%20promised%20to%20move%20to%20India%20to%20live%20with%20him%20as%20he%20was%20unable%20to%20undertake%20a%20similar%20move%20to%20Australia%2C%20owing%20to%20his%20career%20commitments.%20However%2C%20soon%20after%2C%20she%20backtracked%20and%20refused%20to%20move%20as%20it%20would%20force%20her%20to%20give%20up%20custody%20of%20her%20two%20daughters%20to%20her%20ex-husband.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20(Dhawan)%20for%20no%20fault%20of%20his%20own%20had%20been%20through%20immense%20agony%20and%20anguish%20of%20living%20separately%20from%20his%20own%20son%20for%20years.%20Even%20though%20the%20wife%20denied%20the%20allegation%2C%20submitting%20that%20though%20she%20genuinely%20wanted%20to%20live%20in%20India%20with%20him%2C%20yet%20she%20did%20not%20choose%20to%20contest%20the%20claim.%20The%20respondent%2C%20by%20conducting%20herself%20in%20the%20manner%2C%20has%20inflicted%20such%20cruelty%2C%20agony%20and%20trauma%20on%20him%2C%20that%20it%20was%20impossible%20for%20the%20petitioner%20to%20save%20the%20marriage%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BForced%26quot%3B%20to%20pay%20child%20support%2C%20sell%20properties%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Dhawan%20also%20alleged%20that%20Aesha%20forced%20him%20to%20make%20her%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20three%20properties%20that%20the%20cricketer%20bought%20in%20Australia.%20She%20owned%2099%20percent%20of%20one%20of%20the%20properties%20and%20was%20a%20joint%20owner%20in%20the%20other%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20Aesha%20was%20unable%20to%20prove%20that%20she%20did%20not%20compel%20Mr%20Dhawan%20to%20make%20her%20an%20owner%20of%20the%20properties%20and%20she%20also%20contributed%20funds%20towards%20their%20purchase.%20%26quot%3BThe%20respondent%20was%20required%20to%20prove%20that%20properties%20were%20purchased%20out%20of%20her%20fund%20as%20well%20or%20her%20name%20was%20included%20out%20of%20love%20and%20affection.%20Thus%2C%20Dhawan's%20allegation%20that%20she%20compelled%20him%20to%20make%20her%20owner%20to%20some%20extent%20in%20all%20three%20properties%20or%20that%20she%20pocketed%20sale%20proceeds%20thereof%20has%20got%20to%20be%20believed%20as%20true%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20accepted%20Mr%20Dhawan's%20allegations%20that%20Aesha%20forced%20her%20to%20pay%20child%20support%20not%20only%20for%20their%20son%20but%20also%20her%20two