00%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104175819%2Cimgsize-1666722.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Ffukushima-nuclear-plant-starts-second-release-of-treated-radioactive-wastewater-into-the-sea%2Farticleshow%2F104175752.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104175752.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EJapan's%20Fukushima%20nuclear%20power%20plant%20has%20begun%20releasing%20a%20second%20batch%20of%20treated%20radioactive%20wastewater%20into%20the%20sea.%20The%20first%20round%20of%20discharges%20ended%20smoothly%2C%20but%20the%20releases%20have%20been%20strongly%20opposed%20by%20fishing%20groups%20and%20neighboring%20countries%20like%20South%20Korea%20and%20China.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Ffukushima-nuclear-plant-starts-second-release-of-treated-radioactive-wastewater-into-the-sea%2Farticleshow%2F104175752.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Ffukushima-nuclear-plant-starts-second-release-of-treated-radioactive-wastewater-into-the-sea%2Famp_articleshow%2F104175752.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Ffukushima-nuclear-plant-starts-second-release-of-treated-radioactive-wastewater-into-the-sea%2Famp_articleshow%2F104175752.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%20What%20Is%20The%20Case%20Against%20NewsClick%3F%20Facts%20And%20Charges%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ENewsClick%2C%20an%20English-language%20news%20portal%2C%20is%20under%20probe%20for%20alleged%20foreign%20investment%20norms%20violation%20and%20China%20links.%20Its%20founder%2C%20Prabir%20Purakayastha%2C%20and%20HR%20Head%20Amit%20Chakraborty%20were%20arrested%20by%20Delhi%20Police%20under%20the%20anti-terror%20law%20-%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%20-%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20arrests%20came%20a%20day%20after%20raids%20at%20NewsClick%20and%20their%20journalists%2C%20days%20after%20a%20New%20York%20Times%20investigation%20alleged%20the%20news%20portal%20had%20received%20funding%20from%20a%20network%20pushing%20Chinese%20propaganda.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECharges%20Against%20NewsClick%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20against%20NewsClick%20and%20Mr%20Purakayastha%20was%20registered%20on%20August%2017%2C%202023%2C%20with%20UAPA%20invoked%20against%20its%20executives.%20The%20media%20organisation%20has%20been%20charged%20with%20terrorist%20activities%2C%20terror%20funding%20and%20criminal%20conspiracy.%20It%20is%20also%20accused%20of%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20two%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20is%20based%20on%20Rs%2038%20crore%20that%20the%20news%20portal%20had%20allegedly%20received%20as%20foreign%20funding.%20Chinese%20entities%20infused%20funds%20into%20NewsClick%20to%20propagate%20pro-Chinese%20content%2C%20say%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENewsclick%20allegedly%20received%209.6%20crore%20as%20Foreign%20Direct%20Investment%20(FDI)%20in%20April%202018%20from%20the%20US-based%20M%2Fs%20Worldwide%20Media%20Holdings%20LLC%2C%20which%20bought%20its%20shares%20at%20an%20inflated%20premium%20of%2011%2C510%20%2F%20share%2C%20sources%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20was%20incorporated%20in%202017%20by%20Jason%20Pfetcher%2C%20an%20associate%20of%20Neville%20Roy%20Singham%2C%20a%20China%20resident%20who%20is%20reportedly%20a%20contact%20person%20of%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20China.%20He%20allegedly%20infused%20funds%20into%20NewsClick%20to%20promote%20'leftist%20ideology'%2C%20sources%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENewsClick%20also%20allegedly%20received%20export%20remittance%20of%20Rs%2028%20crore%20between%202018%20and%202022%20from%20two%20US-based%20entities.%20But%20it%20couldn't%20produce%20any%20proof%20for%20exporting%20services%20to%20the%20US%20companies%20during%20the%20probe%2C%20sources%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20opaque%20source%20of%20foreign%20funds%20of%20Rs%2038%20crore%20has%20been%20traced%20back%20to%20Neville%20Roy%20Singham%2C%20they%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Were%20The%20Funds%20Used%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EBesides%20infusion%20of%20foreign%20funds%2C%20its%20end%20use%20is%20also%20under%20the%20scanner%20of%20the%20probe%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20investigation%20has%20so%20far%20revealed%20that%20NewsClick%20allegedly%20paid%20Rs%2021%20lakh%20as%20salary%20to%20activist%20Gautam%20Navlakha%2C%20an%20accused%20in%20Bhima%20Koreagon%20case%2C%20according%20to%20the%20agencies.%20Human%20rights%20activist%20Teesta%20Setalvad's%20family%20members%20too%20allegedly%20received%20Rs%2024%20lakh%20as%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENewsclick%20also%20allegedly%20paid%20Rs%2040%20lakh%20as%20salary%20to%20journalist%20Paranjoy%20Guha%20Thakurta%2C%20who%20has%20been%20a%20consultant%20with%20the%20organisation%20since%202018.%20Another%20journalist%2C%20Urmilesh%2C%20received%20Rs%2023%20lakh%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20investigation%20has%20also%20revealed%20that%20Mr%20Purkayastha%20incorporated%20a%20company%20with%20Mr%20Navlakha%20allegedly%20with%20the%20investments%20from%20a%20US-based%20defence%20company%2C%20the%20sources%20say.%20The%20investment%20and%20the%20affairs%20of%20the%20company%20have%20also%20been%20brought%20under%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENewsClick%20Refutes%20Charges%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENewsclick%20said%20it%20has%20been%20targeted%20by%20various%20central%20agencies%20since%202021%20but%20no%20money%20laundering%20complaint%20has%20been%20filed%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20its%20offices%20and%20residences%20of%20officials%20have%20been%20raided%20by%20Enforcement%20Directorate%2C%20the%20Economic%20Offences%20Wing%20of%20Delhi%20Police%20and%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Department.%20%26quot%3BYet%2C%20in%20the%20last%20two%20plus%20years%2C%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20file%20a%20complaint%20accusing%20NewsClick%20of%20money%20laundering%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20organisation%20said%20it%20is%20an%20independent%20news%20website%20and%20denied%20claims%20that%20it%20publishes%20news%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20any%20Chinese%20entity%20or%20authority.%20%26quot%3BNewsclick%20does%20not%20propagate%20Chinese%20propaganda%20on%20its%20website.%20Newsclick%20does%20not%20take%20directions%20from%20Neville%20Roy%20Singham%20regarding%20the%20content%20published%20on%20its%20website%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20has%20asserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPress%20Bodies%20Condemn%20Crackdown%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3ESeveral%20press%20organisations%20have%20condemned%20the%20crackdown%20on%20NewsClick%20and%20stressed%20on%20the%20importance%20of%20independent%20media%20and%20free%20press.%20Journalist%20bodies%20have%20also%20written%20to%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20seeking%20his%20intervention.%20Some%20political%20parties%20too%20have%20come%20out%20in%20support%20of%20the%20news%20portal%20and%20journalists%20who%20were%20raided.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENDTV%20is%20now%20available%20on%20WhatsApp%20channels.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whatsapp.com%2Fchannel%2F0029Va4lixw7z4kcvZI9JM12%5C%22%3EClick%20on%20the%20link%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20all%20the%20latest%20updates%20from%20NDTV%20on%20your%20chat.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696480140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2F9t7e543o_prabir-purkayastha_625x300_04_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-what-is-the-case-against-newsclick-facts-and-charges-4451328%