ulation%20that%20it%20scrapped%20its%20infamous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-is-abandoning-the-one-child-rule-2015-10%23%3A~%3Atext%3DChina%2520is%2520abandoning%2520the%2520one%252Dchild%2520policy%2520after%252035%2520years%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520one%252Dchild%2520policy%2520that%2Cable%2520to%2520have%2520two%2520children.%5C%22%3Eone-child%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202016%20and%20in%202021%20started%20allowing%20couples%20to%20have%20up%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fenglish.scio.gov.cn%2Fin-depth%2F2021-07%2F21%2Fcontent_77641554.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethree%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20push%20doesn't%20appear%20to%20be%20enough%20to%20entice%20people%20to%20have%20more%20babies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20China%20has%20tried%20to%20get%20its%20people%20to%20have%20more%20babies%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Local%20governments%20and%20companies%20are%20offering%20cash%20incentives%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20the%20government%20of%20Hangzhou%2C%20a%20tech%20hub%20in%20East%20China%20and%20home%20to%20the%20e-commerce%20giant%20Alibaba%2C%20started%20granted%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-cities-hangzhou-subsidies-marriage-leave-boost-birth-rate-population-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%2020%2C000%20Chinese%20yuan%2C%20or%20about%20%242%2C800%2C%20as%20a%20one-off%20subsidy%20for%20having%20a%20third%20child%20this%20year.%20Wenzhou%2C%20a%20city%20in%20southeast%20China%2C%20is%20offering%20would-be%20parents%20up%20to%203%2C000%20yuan%20in%20subsidies%20per%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20Chinese%20cities%20and%20provinces%2C%20such%20as%20Shanghai%20and%20the%20major%20coal%20producer%20Shanxi%2C%20also%20increased%20the%20number%20of%20paid%20marriage%20leave%20days%20from%20three%20to%20up%20to%2030.%