%20and%20even%20teachers.%20I%20was%20bullied%20for%20my%20looks.%20I%20started%20isolating%20myself%20and%20developed%20an%20eating%20disorder%20(bulimia).%20I%20lost%20a%20lot%20of%20weight%20due%20to%20this%2C%20but%20even%20then%20I%20was%20shamed%20for%20becoming%20%E2%80%98too%20thin%E2%80%99.%20Today%2C%20I%20look%20back%20and%20realise%20that%20I%20was%20depressed.%20My%20therapy%20sessions%20helped%20me%20uncover%20years%20of%20trauma%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Pooja.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20a%20business%20family%2C%20Pooja%20worked%20in%20their%20chain%20of%20restaurants.%20%E2%80%9CI%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20joint%20family%2C%20but%20I%20never%20shared%20what%20I%20was%20going%20through%20with%20anyone.%20I%20just%20thought%20that%20there%20was%20something%20wrong%20with%20me.%20I%20had%20low%20self-esteem.%20We%20are%20always%20told%2C%20as%20women%2C%20that%20we%20must%20look%20a%20certain%20way%20and%20dress%20a%20certain%20way.%20We%20are%20told%20that%20we%20must%20adjust%20and%20compromise.%20Today%2C%20I%20realise%20how%20important%20it%20is%20for%20us%20to%20talk%20and%20voice%20out%20our%20needs%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20says%20that%20it%20took%20about%20one%20to%20one%20and%20a%20half%20years%20of%20therapy%20for%20her%20to%20feel%20better%20and%20improve%20her%20sleep%20patterns.%20When%20she%20started%20speaking%20to%20her%20friends%20about%20going%20to%20therapy%2C%20they%20would%20ask%20her%20why%20she%20was%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCs0MZy6SHKg%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCs0MZy6SHKg%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3